view.name: Air Quality
view.attribution: Department of Health and Mental Hygiene (DOHMH)
view.description:
Dataset contains information on New York City air quality surveillance data.

Air pollution is one of the most important environmental threats to urban populations and while all people are exposed, pollutant emissions, levels of exposure, and population vulnerability vary across neighborhoods. Exposures to common air pollutants have been linked to respiratory and cardiovascular diseases, cancers, and premature deaths. These indicators provide a perspective across time and NYC geographies to better characterize air quality and health in NYC. Data can also be explored online at the Environment and Health Data Portal: http://nyc.gov/health/environmentdata.

columns.description: Information (such as units) about the measure

columns.name: Geo Type Name
columns.description: Geography type; UHF' stands for United Hospital Fund neighborhoods; For instance, Citywide, Borough, and Community Districts are different geography types

columns.name: Geo Join ID
columns.description: Identifier of the neighborhood geographic area, used for joining to mapping geography files to make thematic maps

columns.name: Time Period
columns.description: Description of the time that the data applies to ; Could be a year, range of years, or season for example

columns.name: Start_Date
columns.description: Date value for the start of the time_period; Always a date value; could be useful for plotting a time series

columns.name: Data Value
columns.description: The actual data value for this indicator, measure, place, and time

columns.name: Message
columns.description: notes that apply to the data value; For example, if an estimate is based on small numbers we will detail here
